Beyonce performed a concert at a wedding celebration in India after being hired by India’s wealthiest man. The singer performed a private concert for the guests of Isha Ambani in Udaipur, Rajasthan on Sunday, as part of the bride-to-be’s pre-wedding festivities. Her set, which reportedly featured several costume changes, spanned hits, including “Crazy in Love” and “Naughty Girl.” The concert was also attended by Hillary Clinton and newlyweds Nick Jonas and Priyanka Chopra. Actor Shah Rukh Khan and cricketer Sachin Tendulkar were also in attendance. Beyonce posted a photo of herself wearing an Indian-inspired outfit on Instagram, with others sharing footage of her performance on Twitter. It’s unknown how much Mukesh Ambani paid her to perform.